  "name": "The Bridge",
  "mood": "Aether",
  "engines": [
    "Ouie"
  ],
  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "VA (feliX, voice 1) + Phase Distortion (Oscar, voice 2). HAMMER=+0.2 — light LOVE. The feliX-Oscar bridge at its most musical: VA's warmth and PD's phase-warped complexity meet in the first territory above neutral where LOVE begins to shape the interaction. At +0.2, neither voice is dominant. PD's phase warp enriches feliX's sine without overwhelming it. This is the productive middle distance — close enough to touch, far enough to remain distinct.",
  "tags": [
    "ouie",
    "va",
    "phase-distortion",
    "felix-oscar",
    "bridge",
    "light-love",
    "aether",
    "balance",
    "musical"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OUIE — The Hammerhead",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "feliX built the bridge. Oscar crossed it halfway. LOVE asked them both to stop there.",
      "At HAMMER=+0.2, the distance is still present. That distance is the music.",
      "The bridge is not the destination. It is where the work happens."
    ],
    "revelation": null,
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "This preset works as a foundation under almost any lead sound. Its neutrality is not blandness — the VA+PD pairing at light LOVE creates a complex spectral bed that supports rather than competes. Try it as a pad layer beneath OBLONG or OVERBITE lead lines.",
    "diagnosis": "VA+PD at HAMMER=+0.2 is deliberately moderate. This is the preset for players who want OUIE's character without its extremes. The PD algoParam at 0.55 creates only moderate phase warp — enough to add upper harmonics without entering distortion territory. BP filter on voice 2 keeps the PD complexity in the midrange. This is the most 'produceable' preset in the Vol 1 set."
  },
